The paper discusses a consensus protocol for a distributed system, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The protocol involves ensuring safety, liveness, and finality, which are key aspects of cryptographic protocols (cs.CR). The use of a directed acyclic graph (DAG) also suggests that the paper could fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The protocol involves communication between nodes, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the protocol, which could also place it under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
